						<summary>

						<p>This much damaged inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1400, Viḷambi, Kanyā, 21, Ādivāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1478 September 20, Sunday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya-Mahārāya-Virūpāksharāya.</hi> It records that, when <hi rend="bold">Viṭṭhararasa-Oḍeya</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūra-rājya,</hi> a certain <hi rend="bold">Mādavayya</hi> made a grant of land, for the service of some god (name lost).</p>						

						</summary>
